solution.p:
We can write x^5 as x \times x \times x \times x \times x. Let's write out the expanded fraction:
\frac{{\color{red}x} \times x \times x \times x \times x}{\color{red}x} \frac{x}{x} \times x \times x \times x \times x x \times x \times x \times x \boxed{x^4}
Let's compare the exponents. x can be written as x^1. We notice that 4 is 5 - 1.
